      <body>
         <div>
            <head>17.12.1881 Samstag</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49097">Ascot</placeName> Dec. 17.
      1881.</p>
            <p>We spent part of the morning in ordering books and burning old ones that
      were no more good. It was delightful to burn the old Latin Grammars. But we
      made such a mess that the Head<note type="reg">
                  <persName key="667">Sneyd-Kynnersley</persName>
               </note> told <persName key="1106">Kylfoyle</persName> to burn them instead of us. The prizes came. We played
      charades in the afternoon the first word was &#x201e;incapable&#x201c;. The
      first scene of the play was a robber pickpocketing two travellers in an
               <hi rend="ul">inn</hi>. In the second the <hi rend="ul">cap</hi> is brought as evidence against
      the robber and in the third his accomplice the waiter informs him that he is
      <hi rend="ul">able</hi> to give him up to the police The second word was
      &#x201e;cardinal&#x201c; but this play was not as good. </p>
         </div>
